 To draw a chessboard in LaTeX using the FEN (Forsyth–Edwards Notation) notation, you can use the `chessboard` package. Here's a sample LaTeX code that demonstrates how to do this:

```latex
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{chessboard}

\begin{document}

\begin{chessboard}
  \setuppiecestyle{
    large,
    fontcolor=\color{black},
    fillcolor=\ifodd\value{piece}\color{white}\else\color{black}\fi
  }
  \setuppositioning{
    filecheck=false,
    squarecheck=false,
    movemark=false,
  }
  \setuppiece[k]{} % Remove the castling rights indicator
  \setuppiece[q]{} % Remove the en passant indicator
  \setuppiece[R]{} % Remove the promotion indicator
  % Set up the FEN notation for the chessboard state
  \fenboard{rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR}
\end{chessboard}

\end{document}
```
This code sets up the `chessboard` package and defines various styles for pieces and positioning. The `fenboard` command is used to set up the FEN notation for the chessboard state. You can modify the FEN notation inside the `fenboard` command to represent any desired state of the chessboard.

